abstract: The president has become increasingly disillusioned with the state where he made his name and with the man who leads it, Governor Andrew Cuomo.

headline_main: William Barr, Coronavirus, Harvey Weinstein: Your Friday Briefing

abstract: Some Democratic rivals question whether Mr. Buttigieg has the experience to be president. Some key episodes in South Bend show how he struggled, learned and grew as a leader.
snippet: Some Democratic rivals question whether Mr. Buttigieg has the experience to be president. Some key episodes in South Bend show how he struggled, learned and grew as a leader.
lead_paragraph: SOUTH BEND, Ind. — The news was alarming: Children in some of South Bend’s poorest neighborhoods had a higher rate of lead poisoning than children in Flint, Mich.

abstract: The same people who should be fixing them.
snippet: The same people who should be fixing them.
lead_paragraph: Every politician condemns the phenomenon of “surprise” medical bills. This week, two committees in the House are marking up new surprise billing legislation. One of the few policy proposals President Trump brought up in this year’s State of the Union address was his 2019 executive order targeting them. In the Democratic debates, candidates have railed against such medical bills, and during commercial breaks, back-to-back ads from groups representing doctors and insurers proclaimed how much the health care sector also abhors this uniquely American form of patient extortion.

abstract: What cool things have we lost because mammoth companies swallowed up innovative start-ups?
snippet: What cool things have we lost because mammoth companies swallowed up innovative start-ups?
lead_paragraph: With all the noisy news flooding the zone in Washington this week — including President Trump doing his best Michael “Fredo, you broke my heart” Corleone in taking out his perceived enemies as if it’s the end of “The Godfather: Part II” — it was easy to miss one of the most important moments in the ever-growing face-off between Big Tech and regulators.

abstract: People should never be punished for things they haven’t done.
snippet: People should never be punished for things they haven’t done.
lead_paragraph: The Department of Homeland Security recently decided to bar New York residents from federal programs that allow “trusted travelers” expedited transit through airports and border checkpoints. The Trump administration is defending the decision as a rational response to New York’s enactment of a law denying federal immigration authorities free access to the state’s motor vehicle records. In truth, the department’s decision is spiteful retaliation against people who reside in a state that declines to bend to the administration’s immigration priorities. Whatever its other virtues or vices, the decision offends constitutional norms that are neither liberal nor conservative but simply American.

abstract: They have been at odds since October, but the tension related to protests in Hong Kong is showing faint signs of easing as the N.B.A. honors its All-Stars.
snippet: They have been at odds since October, but the tension related to protests in Hong Kong is showing faint signs of easing as the N.B.A. honors its All-Stars.
lead_paragraph: The day after Kobe Bryant died, the Chinese ambassador to the United States, Cui Tiankai, posted a statement on Twitter: “Saddened by the tragic loss of #KobeBryant. An inspiration for many and a legend of his generation, he will always be remembered for his contribution to the world of sport and to #ChinaUS people-to-people exchanges.”

abstract: The North has reported no cases of the virus, but relief groups say it is woefully unprepared to deal with an outbreak.
snippet: The North has reported no cases of the virus, but relief groups say it is woefully unprepared to deal with an outbreak.
lead_paragraph: SEOUL, South Korea — The United States said it would approve humanitarian assistance to North Korea to help international aid agencies fight the coronavirus there, amid fears that the impoverished country may be hiding an outbreak.
